class Solution {
    public int findMinimumOperations(String s1, String s2, String s3) {
        int minLen = Math.min(s1.length(), Math.min(s2.length(), s3.length()));
        int commonPrefix = 0;
        while (commonPrefix < minLen && s1.charAt(commonPrefix) == s2.charAt(commonPrefix) && s1.charAt(commonPrefix) == s3.charAt(commonPrefix)) {
            commonPrefix++;
        }
        if (commonPrefix == 0) return -1;
        return s1.length() + s2.length() + s3.length() - 3 * commonPrefix;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the input strings to find the common prefix, then calculates the minimum number of operations required to make the strings equal by deleting characters from the end. It returns -1 if no common prefix is found.
